               <p>THOMAS TAYLOR. I am a <rs id="t18281204-247-viclabel1309" type="occupation">woollen-draper</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18281204-247-victim2147 t18281204-247-viclabel1309"></join>, and live at <placeName id="t18281204-247-crimeloc1310">Pimlico</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18281204-247-crimeloc1310" type="placeName" value="Pimlico"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18281204-247-crimeloc1310" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18281204-247-off1307 t18281204-247-crimeloc1310"></join>. I lost eight Guernsey jackets from the door of my shop, on the 3d of December; I had seen them a quarter of an hour before - I heard a cry in the street; I sent my boy out, and in about twenty minutes he brought back the jackets, and the prisoner; I asked how he came to take<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="182812040126"></xptr>them - he made no reply at first, but afterwards said the other gave them to him; there had been another with him, who escaped.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18281204-247-person2148">
                  JAMES 
                  HAMMOND
               <interp inst="t18281204-247-person2148" type="surname" value="HAMMOND"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18281204-247-person2148" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18281204-247-person2148" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am in the prosecutor's employ. I went into the street. and saw the prisoner and another running - the prisoner had eight Guernsey jackets in his hand- I brought him back with them - it was between eleven and twelve o'clock in the morning; he was about a quarter of a mile from the shop.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18281204-247-person2149">
                  DAVID 
                  JOHNSON
               <interp inst="t18281204-247-person2149" type="surname" value="JOHNSON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18281204-247-person2149" type="given" value="DAVID"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18281204-247-person2149" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I got these jackets at Mr. Taylor's - the prisoner was then in custody; Mr. Taylor asked how he came to take them; he said he did not take them; he was coming from Chelsea, and another boy had them; and when he saw the lad follow him, he threw the jackets to him, and asked him to take them - he said he had done nothing, and did not run.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I was going along Vauxhall-road; I saw a person who asked me to carry this bundle - I put it under my arm; the young man laid hold of my collar, and took me back - the other ran away.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18281204-247-verdict1311" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18281204-247-verdict1311" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 15.</p>
